import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['year'])
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='year', y='people', data=data)
    chart.axhline(y=data['people'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['people'].median()))
    chart.legend()
    return chart

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['age'])
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='age', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['age'].median(), color='red', label=f'Median: {data["age"].median():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['sex'].value_counts().plot(kind='pie', autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=90, shadow=False, legend=True, fontsize=14)
    plt.title('What is the gender distribution of people in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['people'] = pd.to_numeric(data['people'], errors='coerce')
    total_people = data['people'].sum()
    plt.figure(figsize=(8,6))
    sns.barplot(x=['Total People'], y=[total_people], color='blue')
    plt.axhline(total_people, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Total People: {total_people:,.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['people'] = data['people'].astype(int)
    data = data.pivot(index='age', columns='sex', values='people')
    ax = sns.barplot(data=data, x=data.index, y=['M', 'F'], palette=['#4C72B0', '#C44E52'])
    ax.set(xlabel='Age', ylabel='People')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of people by age and gender?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
